{
  "stem": "22979.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 19-- I am going to go when I was 14 years old, in 1938.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was in the schoolyard.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was, I think so.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we started school September, like.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then, suddenly, a siren went up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had to leave the school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "On the radios, we heard that Hitler-- march-- Hitler's troops march over the borders, and they are taking the Sudetenland.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was the Western part of Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then, our school bus closed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when I came home, I heard already talking about, you know, what happened.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the mean time, what I recall, even before '38, we had quite lots of people staying in our house overnight.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Jews from Poland were already crossing the border and escaping from Poland, because they probably were more aware, or people who-- who knew what went on since 1933 in Germany and were escaping.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they came through Slovakia and went further down to Hungary and to Italy, because what I heard, they are going to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At home, because those people were in our house-- sometimes family with children, sometimes only single people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Those were refugees who already left their homeland, Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But you know, when you're 14, I didn't pay too much attention, because my only [LAUGHS] concern was, from school, get home, throw the books away, and go and meet my friends.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So you know, what a teenager-- and I was not interested in these politics.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But then, you know, when we left school, soon after, you know, they kicked out all the Jewish children from school.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was the last time. 1938 I couldn't attend a public school-- no more.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
